<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Bring In and Keep Customers</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1001" relname="joint">The first step to any successful business is promotion and marketing ,</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1003" relname="span">and the second follow-up step is retention .</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1004" relname="span">To learn how to bring in and keep customers can be challenging</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="4" relname="condition">if you have never been exposed to marketing or public relations .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1007" relname="concession">By following a few easy steps , however ,</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1007" relname="contrast">you should be able to not only boost business</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1007" relname="contrast">but keep it steady and/or growing as well .</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1009" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1009" relname="joint">Start with noticeable and recognizable signage .</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1012" relname="span">You want your drive-by traffic to know</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="11" relname="elaboration">who you are and what your business does .</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1011" relname="sequence">Make any day an excuse for an event .</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1015" relname="span">Be it a sale , an anniversary , or an open house ,</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1016" relname="span">celebrate</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1017" relname="joint">by promoting an event</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1017" relname="joint">and opening your doors to the general public .</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1019" relname="span">Offer an incentive</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="18" relname="purpose">to visit or refer your business .</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1021" relname="span">Run a time-sensitive sale or special</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="20" relname="purpose">to drive in traffic .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1023" relname="span">Offer a referral incentive for those</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="22" relname="elaboration">who refer new customers your way .</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1024" relname="joint">Consider print advertising such as the newspaper , magazine , or ads or listings in the phone book .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1025" relname="sequence">Devote time and energy in a website and in maintaining a social networking page for your business .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1026" relname="joint">Both of these tools can be low cost</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="span">and offer you means</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="27" relname="purpose">to keep your name in front of the crowd electronically .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1026" relname="joint">Think about radio or television ads .</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1026" relname="joint">Radio works wonderfully for event-driven exposure ,</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1026" relname="joint">and television can help you build brand recognition .</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1033" relname="span">Network with local professional organizations</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="32" relname="purpose">to build a referral system for year-round leads .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1035" relname="span">Work to keep the customer base</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="34" relname="elaboration">that you have built .</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1026" relname="joint">Start with quality customer service .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1039" relname="span">Be polite and respectful to everyone</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="37" relname="elaboration">who comes in your door ,</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1040" relname="span">and treat that person</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="39" relname="manner">as you would want to be treated .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1042" relname="contrast">Train your staff not only how to be polite</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1042" relname="contrast">but how to successfully do their jobs as well .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1041" relname="joint">Being nice does n't sell your product ,</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1041" relname="joint">nor does it help your staff avoid mistakes .</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1041" relname="joint">Instead , that comes with good training and practice .</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1041" relname="joint">With their permission ,</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1041" relname="joint">sign your customers up for your mailing or email list .</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1041" relname="joint">You can do this in the store or on your website .</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1050" relname="span">Institute a best practices methodology</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="49" relname="elaboration">that includes not selling or sharing the customers ' information with anyone outside of your business .</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1041" relname="joint">Make sure that this policy is shared on your website for full transparency .</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1053" relname="span">Follow up with emails</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="52" relname="purpose">to join your Facebook page ,</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1055" relname="contrast">send a copy of an online newsletter</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1055" relname="contrast">or send emails about upcoming sales or special events .</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1057" relname="contrast">You want to keep your clients engaged in what is going on at your business ,</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1057" relname="contrast">but on the other side be sure not to inundate them .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1059" relname="span">Mail out fliers , hard copy coupons or newsletters</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="58" relname="condition">if the printing and mailing costs are affordable for you .</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1060" relname="span">Always include an opt-out option</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1061" relname="span">so that customers do n't feel</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1062" relname="span">like they are stuck getting your correspondence</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="62" relname="condition">if they do n't really want to .</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1064" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1065" relname="span">Try to boost your search engine status</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="65" relname="means">by embedding pertinent tags into your web pages .</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1064" relname="joint">You should also link your home page to the majority of the pages on your site .</segment>
